Five men are expected to appear in the Athlone Magistrate s Court on Thursday, in connection with the murder of a 22-year-old man, Western Cape police said. Spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said that the five men were arrested on Tuesday morning and are facing a charge of murder. According to information, the suspects stabbed and fatally wounded a 22-year-old man on the night of 19 December 2016 in Crossroads. Police were on patrol when they were called to the scene at midnight at the corner of Imbumba and Moya Street in Crossroads, Rwexana said. On their arrival, police found the victim on the ground with several stab wounds to his body. Informers were activated and since the incident the detectives were tracing the suspects and at about 9am [on Tuesday] they arrested three suspects and two other suspects were caught at about 10am in the Crossroads. 